730339f-b.title: General view - Canal Street - Southwest.
730339f-b.text:
54-58 Canal Street, at the S.W. corner of Orchard Street,
(general view southwestward).
Shown are tenement buildings bisected by the Manhattan Bridge approach, with a backdrop of municipal and financial structures. To the right are the former, circling Foley Square, and to the left are the latter, bordering on Broadway. From left to right, the four predominating structures are: No. 120 Vall St. (American Sugar Refining) Bldg., the Sixty Wall Tower (No. 70 Pine Street), the Singer Pldg., ano the Municipal Bldg. Behind the last appears a portion of the Woolworth Bldg. Thru the center and passing underneath the aforementioned approach, are the tracks of the 3econd avenue Elevated Line.

730338f-a.text:

To the left is Chinatown and beyond are civic structures around Foley Sduare. View 2 shows tenement roofs topped by the Hotel Libby.
